          0,
          "At first glance, that looks like an easy question to answer. It‚Äôs a regularly delivered email with some editorial content, right? Simple! And yet, that description doesn‚Äôt really catch the complexity developing in the form. It‚Äôs a bit like describing a magazine as ‚Äúprinted paper, folded, collated and bound‚Äù: technically accurate, but not truly conveying the complexity of the form."
        ]
      ]
    ],
    [
      1,
      "p",
      [
        [
          0,
          [],
          0,
          "In my experience, most publishers still default to seeing newsletters as a promotional tool: a glorified list of links to bring the readers back to the ‚Äúreal‚Äù product ‚Äî the websites. And sure, that‚Äôs a valuable thing to do. Newsletters are one of the few direct audience engagement tools we have. Getting people to transition from being a search- or social-driven visitor to being one that comes via a newsletter is a huge win."
        ]
      ]
    ],
